properties.name: Louisa Boren Park
properties.sense_of_place: A scenic overlook providing views of Lake Washington, Union Bay, and the Cascade Mountains, imbued with a sense of historical significance due to its namesake’s role as one of Seattle’s founders.
properties.description: A park offering views and historic trees, named after Louisa Boren, one of Seattle’s earliest citizens and a member of the Denny Party.

properties.name: Grand Army of the Republic Cemetery
properties.sense_of_place: A somber, respectful place honoring the sacrifices of Union veterans of the Civil War, connecting the local area to national history.
properties.description: A cemetery established to honor Union veterans of the Civil War, containing graves of soldiers including black soldiers, managed by the Seattle Parks Department.

properties.name: Streissguth Gardens
properties.sense_of_place: An urban oasis offering tranquility and connection to nature, providing a respite from the urban environment.
properties.description: A small urban garden started by the Streissguth family, now owned by the city, providing a quiet, natural space.

properties.name: Frederick Anhalt Apartments
properties.sense_of_place: Distinctive apartments evoke a sense of architectural elegance and European-inspired design, enriching the urban landscape.
properties.description: Apartments designed by Frederick Anhalt in the late 1920s, featuring French Norman inspired elements like turrets and arches.

properties.name: E Valley Street
properties.sense_of_place: Contains a low granite block, a stepping stone. People getting out of horse-drawn carriages would have stepped onto the block and then down to the ground.
properties.description: Contains a low granite block, a stepping stone. People getting out of horse-drawn carriages would have stepped onto the block and then down to the ground.

properties.name: Seattle Asian Art Museum
properties.sense_of_place: A cultural hub displaying Asian art and architectural innovation, inviting contemplation and appreciation of diverse artistic traditions.
properties.description: The original Seattle Art Museum, now housing the Seattle Asian Art Museum, known for its progressive architectural design that broke away from neoclassical styles.

properties.name: Volunteer Park
properties.sense_of_place: A historic public space with recreational features.
properties.description: A historical site purchased by the city for a cemetery in 1876.
